 13. WRITING DATA IN SPARK
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 df.write.format("parquet").mode("overwrite").save("path")

# Write Modes:
  overwrite → Replace existing data
  append    → Add to existing data
  ignore    → Skip if path exists
  error     → Fail if path exists (default)

# File Layout Controls:
  repartition(10)           → increase partitions (full shuffle)
  coalesce(1)               → reduce partitions (no shuffle)
  partitionBy("year","month") → folder-based partitioning (like Hive)
  bucketBy(4,"id")          → bucket into N files per partition
  sortBy("name")            → sort within buckets
  maxRecordsPerFile(10000)  → control records per file

 NOTE: Number of output files = Number of partitions in DataFrame.

