 16. JOIN STRATEGIES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 Broadcast Hash Join
  - Small table (<10MB default) broadcast to all executors.
  - FASTEST join. No shuffle needed.
  - Threshold: spark.sql.autoBroadcastJoinThreshold (default 10MB)
  from pyspark.sql.functions import broadcast
  df1.join(broadcast(df2), "id", "inner")

 Shuffle Hash Join
  - Both tables large → hash partition both → create hash table.
  - Expensive (shuffle + hashing).
  - Use if data distributed uniformly, no skew.
  df1.join(df2.hint("shuffle_hash"), df1.id == df2.id, "inner")

 Sort Merge Join (DEFAULT for large tables)
  - Shuffle → Sort → Merge.
  - Best for large equi-joins consistently.
  - No hint needed (Spark auto-selects).

 Cartesian Join
  - Every row × every row. VERY expensive. Avoid.
  - Non-equi join, no condition needed.

 Broadcast Nested Loop Join
  - Non-equi join with small table broadcastable.
  df1.join(broadcast(df2), df1.id > df2.id, "inner")

