 17. CACHE & PERSIST
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
- Use when same RDD/DataFrame reused multiple times.
- Without cache → Spark recomputes from scratch every Action.

 cache()   = persist(MEMORY_ONLY) → stores as Java objects in RAM.

 Storage Levels:
  MEMORY_ONLY       → RAM only | Objects | Fast | More space
  MEMORY_AND_DISK   → RAM first, evict to disk if full (LRU eviction)
  DISK_ONLY         → Disk only | Serialized | Saves RAM
  MEMORY_ONLY_SER   → RAM | Serialized (smaller footprint, slower read)
  MEMORY_ONLY_2     → 2 replicas on 2 different nodes (fault tolerant)
  OFF_HEAP          → Outside JVM | No GC overhead | Unsafe

 KEY POINTS:
  - Serialized → less memory, more CPU cost.
  - cache() with data > memory → no error, but no caching (silent skip).
  - unpersist() to free memory when done.

