 18. CATALYST OPTIMIZER
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
- Automatic query optimization engine for DataFrame/Dataset.
- NOT available for RDD.

 Steps:
  1. Unresolved Logical Plan   → user code parsed (columns unvalidated)
  2. Resolved Logical Plan     → validated with schema + catalog
  3. Optimized Logical Plan    → rules applied (RBO)
  4. Physical Plans Generated  → multiple execution strategies
  5. Cost-Based Optimization   → best plan selected (CBO)
  6. Execution                 → converted to RDD ops, run on executors

 Key Optimization Rules:
  - Predicate Pushdown   → filters moved closer to data source
  - Projection Pruning   → remove unused columns
  - Constant Folding     → precompute constant expressions
  - Join Reordering      → optimize join sequence
  - Eliminate No-Ops     → remove redundant transformations

