 19. SPARK EXECUTOR MEMORY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 spark.executor.memory = 10GB → actual cluster request = 11GB (+10% overhead)

 Memory Layout:
 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
 │  Memory Overhead (~10% / min 384MB)     │  ← PySpark workers, native
 ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
 │  Reserved Memory (300MB fixed)          │  ← Spark internals
 ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
 │  User Memory (~40%)                     │  ← UDFs, temp objects
 ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
 │  Unified Memory (60%)                   │
 │  ┌──────────────────────────────────┐   │
 │  │ Execution Memory (50% of unified)│   │  ← shuffles, joins, sorts
 │  ├──────────────────────────────────┤   │
 │  │ Storage Memory  (50% of unified) │   │  ← cache, broadcast vars
 │  └──────────────────────────────────┘   │
 └─────────────────────────────────────────┘

 KEY POINTS:
  - Execution OOM → task FAILS (no eviction fallback).
  - Storage OOM   → LRU cached blocks evicted (no failure).
  - Execution can borrow from Storage if nothing cached (and vice versa).
  - Shuffle-heavy → set spark.memory.storageFraction=0.2
  - Cache-heavy   → set spark.memory.storageFraction=0.7
  - Off-Heap      → outside JVM, no GC overhead, Tungsten-optimized.

